The mother of Michelle Knight, the third woman rescued from a basement where she had been held captive for more than a decade, says she carried on the search alone for years because police gave up on the case.

While the stories of missing Cleveland girls Gina DeJesus and Amanda Berry have remained high-profile cases over the last decade, little is known of third captive Michelle.

As yet, no picture has been published of Michelle, either from the time she went missing or since her discovery.Â 

While family appeals for Gina and Amanda have been frequent and well-publicised over the past ten years, her case appears to have been long forgotten.

